<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,919,1558]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1243,1270]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Elytra" baseAuthorityName="Lea" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[327,525,1244,1270]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Aquilonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costata">
<emphasis box="[327,525,1244,1270]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Aquilonia costata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is now known from Cape York Peninsula and near bodies of water in the 
<collectingRegion country="Australia" name="Northern Territory" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Northern Territory</collectingRegion>
, almost all of which are popular tourist destinations. It is the only Australian species with a colour pattern of yellowish orange dorsum with black tipped elytral apices. In the immediate study area close to the northern coast line of 
<collectingCountry box="[231,334,1351,1377]" name="Australia" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Australia</collectingCountry>
this colour pattern resembles 
<emphasis box="[677,854,1352,1378]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
Aquil. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[753,854,1352,1377]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Aquilonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="messoria">messoria</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
c 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[874,992,1352,1378]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">omb. nov.</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1048,1298,1352,1378]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
Aquil. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[1124,1298,1352,1378]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Aquilonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similismessoria">similismessoria</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
c 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1319,1436,1352,1378]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">omb. nov.</emphasis>
(from coastal New 
<collectingCountry box="[372,453,1387,1413]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Guinea</collectingCountry>
near Buna Bay and surrounding islands), and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[987,1186,1388,1414]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pacifica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="russellia">
<emphasis box="[987,1186,1388,1414]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Pacifica russellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1203,1399,1387,1414]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
). It differs 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[230,353,1424,1450]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pacifica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="russellia">
<emphasis box="[230,353,1424,1450]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">P. russellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of an arched 
<date box="[675,709,1424,1450]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">V7</date>
posterior to the LO, T8 is without any median ridges and the ML without lateral teeth. A single female found flying with males is macropterous and coloured as for the male. Larval specimens with laterally explanate tergal margins from Prince of 
<collectingCountry box="[892,1036,1495,1521]" name="Wales Island" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Wales Island</collectingCountry>
in the Torres Strait were scored by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" box="[151,484,1531,1558]" firstAuthor="Ballantyne" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="1 - 162" refId="ref114597" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. L. (2013) Systematics and phylogenetics of Indo-Pacific Luciolinae fireflies (Coleoptera: Lampyridae) and the description of new genera. Zootaxa, 3653 (1), 1 - 162. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3653.1.1" type="journal article" year="2013">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin (2013</bibRefCitation>
, 
<tableCitation box="[495,579,1531,1558]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="39.[151,239,370,394]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="TABLE 2. Pronotal colour patterns of Abs. pallescens comb. nov. M = male; F = female. Pronotal colour in brackets: 1 = yellow; 2 = restricted median brown markings; 3 = extensive median brown markings; 4 = indeterminate, colour could be due to retraction of underlying muscles (difficulty experienced in interpretation of pinned specimens only)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/B0EB4882511C1871FF0EFEEDED521DB0" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" tableUuid="B0EB4882511C1871FF0EFEEDED521DB0">Table 2</tableCitation>
) (QMBA) but are not reliably associated..
</paragraph>
